布兰登·弗劳尔斯 (Brandon Flowers) 讨论俄罗斯事件，称他已废弃 Killers 新专辑https://www.nme.com/news/music/brandon-flowers-discusses-Russia-incident-says-hes-scrapped-new-killers-album-3489124?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=brandon-flowers-discusses-俄罗斯事件称他废弃了新杀手专辑Will RichardsSun, 27 Aug 2023 07:59:30 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndie https://www.nme.com/?p=3489124 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="杀手们" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我认为你不会再看到我们制作这种类型的音乐了”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brandon-flowers-discusses-russia-incident-says-hes-scrapped-new-killers-album-3489124">布兰登·弗劳尔斯 (Brandon Flowers) 的帖子讨论了俄罗斯事件，称他已废弃 Killers 的新专辑，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="杀手们" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/20230826_PHELPS_THE_KILLERS_READING_FESTIVAL_READING_124042-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-killers">Killers</a>主唱布兰登<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/brandon-flowers">·弗劳尔斯 (Brandon Flowers)</a>表示，他已经中途放弃了乐队的新专辑。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/the-killers-reading-festival-2023-review-setlist-photos-3489163">雷丁节上的杀手：纯粹的维加斯表演技巧——以及青少年鼓的轰动</a></strong></li></ul><p>乐队本周带着<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-the-killers-synth-heavy-new-song-your-side-of-town-3488438">新单曲“Your Side Of Town”</a>回归，这是乐队今年的第一首单曲，也是他们自<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-the-killers-anthemic-new-song-boy-3284083">去年独立单曲“Boy”</a>以来的首张专辑。</p><p>然而，在接受<em><a href="https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/7439f78a-4108-11ee-9be5-c37fa3a5fe8b?shareToken=4f22f3a84e8f8aa8ef601e11e1279cad" target="_blank" rel="noopener">《泰晤士报》</a></em>采访时，弗劳尔斯透露，乐队计划的新专辑已被取消。</p><p> “录音进行到一半时，我意识到，‘我不能这样做，’”弗劳尔斯说道，并补充道：“这不是那种唱片……我认为这将是……我认为你不会看到我们制作不再有这种类型的音乐了。”</p><p>他补充道：“这就是我所处的危机。杀手是我的身份，我们的歌曲占据了席位，但我更满足于制作像[2021年专辑] <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/the-killers-pressure-machine-review-3017509">‘Pressure Machine’</a>这样的音乐。”</p><p> “我发现自己在写这本书时有着坚强的一面。这就是我一直在寻找的人！我为‘Hot Fuss’感到自豪，就像你为 20 岁时所做的事情感到自豪一样，但我还不到 20 岁。所以我正在考虑我人生的下一个阶段。”</p><p>谈到乐队的未来，他继续说道：“我现在是一个不同的人，很难回去，”并补充说他想为较小的场地制作更安静的音乐。</p><p> “这是一场冲突，”他补充道。 “只是，好吧，我什么时候做出改变？乐队里谁也想这么做？ No matter what, there will always be people who look at me and just think of <i>Somebody Told Me</i> . And I get that. But I&#39;m interested in evolving.” </p><figure id="attachment_3488439" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3488439" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3488439" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/the-killers@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3488439" class="wp-caption-text"> The Killers. CreditL Anton Corbijn</figcaption></figure><p> Elsewhere in the interview, Flowers discussed a recent incident at a show in Georgia, where <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/the-killers-apologise-after-being-booed-for-bringing-russian-fan-onstage-in-georgia-3483586">the band were booed by the crowd by inviting a Russian fan onstage</a> .</p><p> Introducing the fan, frontman Brandon Flowers told the crowd: “We don&#39;t know the etiquette of this land but this guy&#39;s a Russian. You OK with a Russian coming up here?” before he was greeted with boos from the audience.</p><p> “I had to calm an impossible situation,” he told <em>The Times</em> . “We want our concerts to be communal and I had no idea words I was taught my entire life to represent a unity of the human family could be taken as being pro-Russian occupation. We&#39;re sad how this played out.”</p><p> After the show, The Killers wrote in a statement: “Good people of Georgia, it was never our intention to offend anyone! We have a longstanding tradition of inviting people to play drums and it seemed from the stage that the initial response from the crowd indicated that they were okay with tonight&#39;s audience participation member coming onstage with us.</p><p> “We recognize that a comment, meant to suggest that all of the Killers&#39; audience and fans are &#39;brothers and sisters&#39; could be misconstrued. We did not mean to upset anyone and we apologize. We stand with you and hope to return soon.”</p><p> Last night (August 26), the band headlined <a href="https://www.nme.com/reading-festival-2023">Reading Festival</a> and performed the same trick, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-killers-invite-fan-to-play-drums-with-them-at-reading-2023-3489069">inviting a fan on stage to play drums on &#39;For Reasons Unknown&#39;</a> .</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/the-killers-reading-festival-2023-review-setlist-photos-3489163">Reviewing the band&#39;s set</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “The Killers take us to church for their second R&amp;L headline set, and one that very much fits Flowers&#39; bill as a masterclass from some real monsters of rock (brought to you, of course, “by way of the Fabulous Las Vegas, Nevada”).”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brandon-flowers-discusses-russia-incident-says-hes-scrapped-new-killers-album-3489124">Brandon Flowers discusses Russia incident, says he&#39;s scrapped new Killers album</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
